Round 1
[Patient] What foods can I eat to help manage my heart failure?
[Educator] Focus on fruits, veggies, whole grains, lean protein, and healthy fats.

Round 2
[Patient] Can I still enjoy soul food favorites like fried chicken?
[Educator] Limit fried foods and opt for baked, grilled, or roasted options instead.

Round 3
[Patient] How about sodium intake? Any tips on reducing it?
[Educator] Cut back on processed foods, canned soups, and fast food to lower sodium intake.

Round 4
[Patient] Are there any specific foods that can worsen heart failure?
[Educator] High-sodium foods, processed meats, sugary drinks, and excessive alcohol can worsen heart failure.

Round 5
[Patient] What about snacks? Any heart-healthy options you recommend?
[Educator] Opt for nuts, seeds, fruits, veggies, yogurt, or whole grain crackers as snacks.

Round 6
[Patient] How can I make sure I'm getting enough fiber in my diet?
[Educator] Include plenty of fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and legumes in your meals.

Round 7
[Patient] Are there any cooking methods I should avoid for heart health?
[Educator] Limit deep frying and choose healthier cooking methods like baking, grilling, or steaming.

Round 8
[Patient] Can I still enjoy desserts or should I cut them out completely?
[Educator] Enjoy desserts in moderation and opt for healthier choices like fruit-based desserts.

Round 9
[Patient] Should I be concerned about my caffeine intake?
[Educator] Limit caffeine intake and opt for decaf or herbal teas as alternatives.

Round 10
[Patient] What about portion sizes? Any tips on controlling them?
[Educator] Use smaller plates, listen to your body's hunger cues, and avoid oversized portions.

Round 11
[Patient] Are there any specific foods that can help improve heart health?
[Educator] Incorporate heart-healthy foods like salmon, walnuts, berries, and leafy greens into your diet.

Round 12
[Patient] How can I stay hydrated while managing my heart failure?
[Educator] Drink plenty of water throughout the day and limit sugary drinks and excessive caffeine.

Round 13
[Patient] Should I be following a specific diet plan for heart failure?
[Educator] Aim for a balanced diet rich in fruits, veggies, whole grains, lean protein, and healthy fats.

Round 14
[Patient] Any tips on reading food labels to make healthier choices?
[Educator] Look for low-sodium, low-fat, and high-fiber options when reading food labels.

